obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (32073)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00028_191810_1523342873787&sectionId=32073&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00028_191810_1523342873787
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called Usurious Loans Act, 1918.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except ^1[the territories which, immediately before the 1st`
  line `November, 1956, were comprised in Part B States] ^2***.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that it shall not apply to`
  line `any area, class of persons, or class of transactions which it may specify in its notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. (No. 3) 1956, for "Part B States".`
  line
  line `2. The words "including British Baluchistan" omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (32074)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 1926, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00028_191810_1523342873787&sectionId=32074&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00028_191810_1523342873787
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(1) "Interest" means rate of interest and includes the return to be made over and above what was`
  line `actually lent, whether the same is charged or sought to be recovered specifically by way of interest or`
  line otherwise.
  line
  line `(2) "Loan" means a loan whether of money or in kind and includes any transaction which is, in`
  line `the opinion of the Court, in substance a loan.`
  line
  line `(3) "Suit to which this Act applies" means any suit--`
  line
  line `(a) for the recovery of a loan made after the commencement of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) for the enforcement of any security taken or any agreement, whether by way of settlement`
  line `of account or otherwise, made, after the commencement of this Act, in respect of any loan made`
  line `either before or after the commencement of this Act; ^1[or`
  line
  line `(c) for the redemption of any security given after the commencement of this Act in respect of`
  line `any loan made either before or after the commencement of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (32075)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Re-opening of transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00028_191810_1523342873787&sectionId=32075&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00028_191810_1523342873787
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything in the Usury Laws Repeal Act, 1855`
  line `(28 of 1855), where, in any suit to which this Act applies, whether heard ex parte or otherwise, the Court`
  line `has reason to believe, --`
  line
  line `(a) that the interest is excessive; and`
  line
  line `(b) that the transaction was, as between the parties thereto, substantially unfair, the Court may`
  line `exercise all or any of the following powers, namely, may,--`
  line
  line `(i) re-open the transaction, take an account between the parties, and relieve the debtor of all`
  line `liability in respect of any excessive interest;`
  line
  line `(ii) notwithstanding any agreement, purporting to close previous dealings and to create a new`
  line `obligation, re-open any account already taken between them and relieve the debtor of all liability`
  line `in respect of any excessive interest, and if anything has been paid or allowed in account in respect`
  line `of such liability, order the creditor to repay any sum which it considers to be repayable in respect`
  line thereof;
  line
  line `(iii) set aside either wholly or in part or revise or alter any security given or agreement made`
  line `in respect of any loan, and if the creditor has parted with the security, order him to indemnify the`
  line `debtor in such manner and to such extent as it may deem just:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the exercise of these powers, the Court shall not--`
  line
  line `(i) re-open any agreement purporting to close previous dealings and to create a new`
  line `obligation which has been entered into by the parties or any persons from whom they claim at`
  line `a date more than ^1[twelve] years from the date of the transaction;`
  line
  line `(ii) do anything which affects any decree of a Court.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In the case of a suit brought on a series of transactions the expression "the transaction"`
  line `means, for the purposes of proviso (i), the first of such transactions.`
  line
  line `(2) (a) In this section "excessive" means in excess of that which the Court deems to be reasonable`
  line `having regard to the risk incurred as it appeared, or must be taken to have appeared, to the creditor at the`
  line `date of the loan.`
  line
  line `(b) In considering whether interest is excessive under this section, the Court shall take into account`
  line `any amounts charged or paid, whether in money or in kind, for expenses, inquiries, fines, bonuses,`
  line `premia, renewals or any other charges, and if compound interest is charged, the periods at which it is`
  line `calculated, and the total advantage which may reasonably be taken to have been expected from the`
  line transaction.
  line
  line `(c) In considering the question of risk, the Court shall take into account the presence or absence of`
  line `security and the value thereof, the financial condition of the debtor and the result of any previous`
  line `transactions of the debtor, by way of loan, so far as the same were known, or must be taken to have been`
  line `known, to the creditor.`
  line
  line `(d) In considering whether a transaction was substantially unfair, the Court shall take into account all`
  line `circumstances materially affecting the relations of the parties at the time of the loan or tending to show`
  line `that the transaction was unfair, including the necessities or supposed necessities of the debtor at the time`
  line `of the loan so far as the same were known, or must be taken to have been known, to the creditor.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Interest may of itself be sufficient evidence that the transaction was substantially`
  line unfair.
  line
  line `(3) This section shall apply to any suit, whatever its form may be, if such suit is substantially one for`
  line `the recovery of a loan or for the enforcement of any agreement or security in respect of a loan ^2[or for the`
  line `redemption of any such security].`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall affect the rights of any transferee for value who satisfies the Court`
  line `that the transfer to him was bona fide, and that he had at the time of such transfer no notice of any fact`
  line `which would have entitled the debtor as against the lender to relief under this section. For the purposes of`
  line `this sub-section, the word "notice" shall have the same meaning as is ascribed to it in section 4 of the`
  line `Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882).`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall be construed as derogating from the existing powers or jurisdiction of`
  line `any Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 1926, s. 3, for "six".`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 3, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (32076)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Insolvency proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00028_191810_1523342873787&sectionId=32076&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00028_191810_1523342873787
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `On any application relating to the admission or amount of a proof of a`
  line `loan in any insolvency proceedings, the Court may exercise the like powers as may be exercised under`
  line `section 3 by a Court in a suit to which this Act applies.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
